commit.message:
Fix require calls for bundler

We do own instanciation for gem tasks and don't require gem_tasks any longer.
Update release date in History.md
Add History update annotated tags and pushing of windows binary gems to release task.

Use default RUBY_CC_VERSION from rake-compiler-dock.

It defines 2.0 to 2.4, which is fine for us.
Update History.md
Sort c files for fptr struct generation and cleanup fptr files.
Refresh fptr struct due to the previous commit

Preserve the call convention (APIENTRY) for function pointers.

Fixes SEGFAULTs on Windows i686.
Update rake-compiler and rake-compiler dock to support ruby upto 2.4
Build fptr struct with parallel rake tasks
Fix call convention for wglGetProcAddress on Windows-i686
Fix warning: overflow in implicit constant conversion
Remove duplicated BINDINGS_VERSION definition.
Update the README
Update to rake-compiler-dock-0.5.0 for Ruby-2.3 cross build.

Merge pull request #15 from bendiken/redbook-examples

Fix Ruby 2.0 compatibility of RedBook examples
Update my email.
store fptr_struct.h in git, to allow bundle install from git.
Replace hoe by bundler
Ensured that all RedBook examples are compatible with Ruby 2.0+.
Add gem:windows task for building binary windows gems per rake-compiler-dock.
Add some files to clean task.
Add glext.h from the Mesa project.
Use rb_path2class() instead of module parameter, because the receiver can be different to 'Gl'.
Add OpenGL-3.0 vertex array functions.
Use GL_PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER instead of _ARB version.
Segfault in Mesa is fixed now.
Fix TestOpenGLBuffer#test_write_unmapped .
Fix test for glGetActiveAttribARB.
